location.address: Rumah Genjing, Jl. Pramuka Raya No. 56, Cempaka Putih, Jakarta

photo.caption: Udang Saos Padang & Kepiting Jumbo Saos Padang

review.review_text: Sekedar review  - makanan disajikan dingin - bahan tidak fresh ( frozen ) - tidak ada keterangan harga /ons atau apapun, ujung2 nya harga kepiting berbeda sama yg di promosikan. - pesan 1 paket milob tp tidak ada lobster , gak ada pemberitahuan sama sekali, pas ditanya habis, sudah diganti dengan kerang padahal "kerang" sudah termasuk dalam paket. - pesan 1 kepiting super jumbo, pas dimakan bau tengik. alhasil saya mengalami diare selama 3 hari setelah makan disana. overall dari segi kualitas dan service benar2 mengecewakan. Guys please don't come to this place!

Parah, pesen paket kerang rame2, 145k, judulnya rame2 tapi buat berdua kurang. Kerang nya cuma satu jenis yaitu kerang ijo, ukuran banyak yg mini bgt, ada juga kerang yg rusak (bau). Cumi cuma satu ekor dipotong jd banyak. Intinya ga worth it buat harga segitu. Definetely won't gonna come back.

Makan yg di bintaro gak sempet foto. Pesen mitinf combo isinya kepiting sama kerang cumi udang saos padang level pedes. Pedesnya beneran pedes bgt kalau yg gbs makan cabe jgn pesen. Menurut ku mayan fresh seafood dan gak kopong. Enak deh. Saosnya sih yg juara, melimpah smpe tumpah2. Oh ya ada jagungnya juga. Nikmat.  Harganya 190 rb an. ok lah.   Selamat mencoba!

Setelah beberapa lama akhirnya baru sempet nyobain miting lobster yg sempat terkenal beberapa waktu lalu..  pas dateng, masuk ke dalem, disambut rasa bau yg aga menyengat. Kita tau seafood pasti amis. Tp ga seamis ini..  mesen menu di kasir. Tp smua abis. Tinggal kepiting 150gr kecil. Cumi. Udang. Kerang. lobsternya abis. Pdhl baru jem 6.30 malam.  hrg sih sangat bersahabat. Makan 1 kepiting 150gr ama udang cuma 65ribu.  pas dateng makanannya, kita cobain. ini kayaknya makanan yang diangetin deh. Rasanya GAK FRESH banget. bahkan rasa saus padangny aja rada dingin. pdhl br disajiin.  Kita makan. utk taste ny standart. tapi utk tekstur daging kpitingnya aneh bgt. Lembek. Ky tahu jepang.... blm pernah makan ky gini. udangnya jg ky angetan.  SMOGA GA KENAPA2 DEH. KITA MAKAN GA ABIS. Takut

Pertama kali ksni dlu mau ksni awal buka krna rame cancel Mulu skrng pas sepi nyoba dan SUMPAH KECEWA  Makanan ga ada yg seger dari udang kerang apalagi kepiting nya ga bersih dan ga seger .. saya ga bohong pas pulang langsung kyk gatel gremet" dan akhir nya minum kelapa ijo .. Saya sangat menyarankan yaa ini makanan seafood smua resiko Klo ga seger apa lagi Frozen food itu bisa membahayakan org yg sensitif kyk saya .. Klo emng itu Frozen ya Mongo di masakin yg bener disajikan panas bgt atau smpe beneran Mateng gitu ini pas smpe meja dingin dan rasanya ga karuan bumbu nya ga pas smua ..  Ga akan balik lagi dan ga mau si balik lg trauma bgt

restaurant.name: The Coffee Club

location.address: Knox O-Zone, 425 Burwood Highway, Wantirna, Melbourne

restaurant.timings: 8 AM to 10 PM (Mon-Wed), 8 AM to 10:30 PM (Thu-Sat), 9 AM to 10 PM (Sun)

review.review_text: Had a quick brekky. Portions was ok. But bit pricey. Loved the coffee. Good and friendly customer service.

Decided to go here after dinner with some friends to have a coffee & cake. It had been quite a while since we had last been here and were quite disappointed when we ordered our desserts. The portions were tiny! Probably 1/3 of the slice that was given to us when we have come here previously  and were told weâ€™d have to pay extra if we wanted ice cream instead of cream - last time we had a choice. We actually wondered if it had changed hands as the service was not good with the waiter very confused about what desserts were available and the cakes didnâ€™t taste great either. Wonâ€™t be back.

caught up with a friend tonight and we couldnâ€™t agree on what sort of food we fancied, so we went with the coffee club knox which offers a variety of cuisines.   We ordered the chicken club sandwich and chips and a bowl of nachos and shared.   The chicken club sandwich was fresh and the chicken moist. I think however I preferred the nachos, this version is the one I prefer, not to over the top with cheese and ingredients. Crunchy chips you can dip and not soggy. despite comments in other reviews service was actually quite quick and friendly. Good spot for tasty basic food. Canâ€™t vouch for the coffee.  KD

Came here a couple of months back and didn't have a good experience. Came back again hoping it had changed. Unfortunately it was exactly the same as last time. Seems like all the food prepared in advance and nothing is cooked fresh. Also highly overpriced. Ordered a Caesar salad, sweet potato bowl and omlette. All extremely underwhelming! Will not be returning!  Just to note that this is not consistent across all coffee clubs as I gave been to others and they have been great.

Have been disappointed each time I come here. I keep trying to give them a chance but always get let down. Avg coffee, avg food, rude staff who are not helpful at all and terrible wait times. Being in such a prime location too, it is a bit disappointing not that no improvement has been made.

Cheap crowd wearing sleepers, over priced drinks and food, food was not tasty too, No water in the bathroom. Spotted some call girls too. ðŸ‘¯â€â™€ ......

The cheapest trick this place plays is that it won't accept your booking on zomato on the pretext that it's overcrowded but actually it's empty in fact.. Why I rated its 1 star cause there is nothing less than 1 star. I would give it -10 star why cause its not a club in reality, in fact its more of a red light area club. I left the place in 10 mins so nothing much to review. Everyone stay away from this place.

review.review_text: DO NOT GO HERE! Cheap place , Cheap staff, Food sucks , drinks sucks.This place must be reported to be removed. They are jus trying to scam you.Lot of better places nearby. We orderd food n drinks , we got neither after waiting for close to one hour and then  when we finally got fed up and started walking out they wanted us to pay the bill.We paid for the water n left.Look at other reviews here all are similar.Do not ever ever go here.I wish I coule give it a negative rating.

I dont why this place even exists on Church street. A friend of mine took me here last month, they serve cheap booze compared to surrounding listings. The food was terrible, thre french fries still had the frozen odour and taste. The chinese starters very pathetic. I didnt feel the drinks were genuine either. Avoid is my call on this restaurant Ambiance: 3/5 Food: 1.5/5 Staff: 3.5/5 Value for money: 3/5

We were walking by and found this place, we were the only ones there, I should have guessed, but since we were there wanted to try dining here, the ambience is pretty ok, the lighting is horrendous. Although there weren't any people, the food we ordered was super delayed and it did not come as a saviour, coz the food wasn't great to be ok with the delay.
This place doesn't deserve to be called a pub. . Interior is like some horror movie. . Poorly lit Interior. . . Service ok, food ok. . No dedicated smoking zone. Have to go out for smoking. .

location.address: 3rd Floor, Food Court, Ambience Mall, DLF Phase 3, Gurgaon

review.review_text: Worst Chinese food in city. Seriously how could someone cook so horrible.

We ordered Chilli Potato ..... eeehhhh ...... too sweet and too crispy than it was needed ...... if i wanted sweet i would have ordered honey chili potato.  Delivery time was 10 mins max. Staff was sweet and friendly. Quantity was okish according to price but taste was not upto the mark.
Okay, so i ordered Schezwan Noodles from here and it was too spicy. The taste was blend it was just more of spice. I always try chinese food wherever i go, but this was disappointing.

I had this non veg platter, which costs around â‚¹900. To be frank I was not content. Portions were ample for about 3 people however it's the taste that actually killed my appetite. Kind of burnt flavour which did not definitely go well with the fried rice as well as the noodles.

The food here tastes pretty great! We ordered a sriracha paneer skewer sizzler (noodles option). Would give it 5/5 since the quantity was good, and the flavours amazing. The noodles were cooked just right, Manchurian balls and gravy were both delicious, and the sriracha paneer took the crown.

restaurant.name: Tokyo Ramen

location.address: Shop 3503, Level 2 Upper, Macquarie Centre, Corner Of Herring Road And Waterloo Road, Macquarie Park, Sydney

restaurant.timings: 10 AM to 7 PM (Mon-Wed, Fri-Sat), 10 AM to 9 PM (Thu), 10 AM to 6 PM (Sun)

review.review_text: Service was quite poor. I asked if they have tonkatsu broth and they straight out said no and pointed to katsu don option...I asked for ramen, why are you giving me crumbed chicken on rice? I then proceeded to pay for my meal in card, and when the ladg gave me the receipt, she did not even say thank you or look at me. Simply looked away whilst handing me the receipt. I would understand it if she was serving another customer or helping kitchen staff but no apparently.  I only rate this 3 stars because: - ramen broth was good. - resto was clean. - waiting time was good. - portion was the right size.  Noodles can be done better and I would love it if they consider adding tonkatsu ramen broth to their menu. I would also consider improving level of service. I know it's located on a busy shopping centre but as a business, they could earn more profit with simply more smiles, thank you, and friendliness in responding to customers' enquiries :)
Donâ€™t waste your money! Instant noodle is better than this place. Please can you just close your shop. I donâ€™t know why people would eat here
I believe they just pour soy sauce into water and name it ramen soup. I would suggest stop serving these if they donâ€™t know what they are doing.
Wrost Katsu Don Iâ€™ve ever eaten. Worst. If I can rate 0, I will definitely rate 0. way too much sugar for a Katsu Don. The Ramen, the soup is like water.......

Will give 0 if I can, I ordered one ramen and one serve of jioza, I paid for my lunch and started waiting. I waited so long(ordered at 11.55 AM, when i leave it is 1:26 PM) and my lunch was not served, when i decide to leave, the waiters are ignoring me and mother fking pretending that I do not exist!  I did not get my payment back and i did not had my meal, in the past I got hairs in my soup, I got iron wires in my soup, and the soup tastes funny(salty as hell or the opposite) I will complain about this in food safety NSW as well. If you went there, welcome to suffer!
